cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.AI

The paper deals with network interdiction, which is a topic related to network security and optimization. The use of adversarial traffic flows also suggests a focus on cybersecurity. Therefore, cs.NI (Network and Distributed Systems Security) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the study of algorithms and complexity, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of optimization techniques and the analysis of approximation ratios could also place the paper in cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
